    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a bit scary to read. It sounds like they could come after me for a lot of money if there's even a small mistake. Are there any \"hidden\" ways this could get worse? Like, are there specific things in that wording that act as traps for a freelancer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The phrases \"negligent or more culpable act or omission\" and \"recklessness or willful misconduct\" are key areas to watch out for. \"Negligent\" sets a relatively low bar, meaning almost any mistake could be covered by this clause. \"Willful misconduct\" holds you to the highest standard, proving you intentionally caused harm. Always try to limit this clause or specify that it only applies to gross negligence to reduce your risk.",
      "source": "target",
